document.content:
Software Architecture & System Design: I wish I had known about this earlier…

As a non-technical person, I was always struggling to understand the under-the-hood side of applications. It got better over time: thanks to various books, articles, meetups, my technical friends, and, of course, one Java developer who is also my husband :)


Important notes

The story is entirely based on Artur Ejsmont’s expertise and knowledge. I don’t pretend to be a technical expert which I’m not (at least for now 😏).


What I share in this story is very limited. When reading the book, I prepared the abstract for myself that took 20 Google Docs pages. If you want to improve your understanding of software architecture, I would recommend reading the book, preparing the abstract, and discussing what you have learned with a technical friend or colleague.

﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿
